  "text": "Although ligands and receptors of the Wnt-1/wg signaling pathway are coexpressed in certain tissues, the outcome of a signaling event depends on various factors outside the cell. Wnts are secreted proteins bound to extracellular matrix molecules and genetic analyses in Drosophila revealed the signi®cance of glycosaminoglycans for Wnt-1/wg signaling (summarized by [CITATION_1] . Although the involvement of heparan sulfate proteoglycans (HSPG) in Xenopus mesoderm differentiation is known [CITATION_2] , experiments which specify the binding of individual growth factors, e.g. Xwnt-8, are lacking. It is speculated that HSPG may be required to establish gradients or to enhance signaling (see Cumberledge and Reichsman, 1997).",
